You are given an integer 'n'function to calculate and
return the sum of the digits in 'n' after converting it to its binary
representation.
For example, 15, which has a binary representation of 1111, should
return 4.

Answers ------
import java.util.Scanner;
public class Asish{
    
         public static int sumOfBinaryDigits(int n) {
       int sum =0;
       while( n >0){
           sum += n &1;
           n>>=1;
       }
       return sum;
    }
    
    
    public static void main(String args[]){
        int n = 15;
        int result = sumOfBinaryDigits(n);
        System.out.println(result);
    }
}

